"tutorial.got_it" = "Got it";
"tutorial.dont_show_again" = "Show this guide at startup";
"tutorial.hint_score" = "Your score";
"tutorial.hint_grid" = "Tap a column to launch a block. The goal is to make chains of 5 blocks of the same color.";
"tutorial.hint_brix" = "From time to time, a special block appears (a brix) with a number on it. This brix does not disappear the same way: make chains nearby (5) to reduce the number little by little...";
"tutorial.hint_queue" = "Here are the next blocks you can launch. Every 10 blocks you place, a line drops in to shake up your stack.";
"tutorial.hint_bomb" = "You can use a bomb when you have one left. It clears a big area!";
"rules.show_guides_at_start" = "Show guides when a match starts";
"tutorial.page1_title" = "Goal of the game";
"tutorial.page1_body" = "The goal of the game is to get the highest score. To score points, use blox (coloured stones) and place them into the grid (from the bottom up) to form \"chains\" of 5 blox of the same colour. The chains score points and vanish, making room for the next blox.";
"tutorial.page1_chain_caption" = "= chain → points!";
"tutorial.page2_title" = "Not that easy!";
"tutorial.page2_body" = "The game would be too easy if all you had to do was make colour chains. Every 10 blox, a random line drops in and disrupts your stack. And best of all: there is a 1-in-8 chance that a blox mutates before you can launch it and becomes a Brix. This special stone, marked with a number, cannot be cleared like the others — you need to form chains nearby (5) to make it disappear. Fortunately you have bombs (one at the start, and a new one every 10 chains): a bomb destroys the 9 cells around its impact point and clears Brix in one hit!";
"tutorial.page3_title" = "Your turn!";
"tutorial.page3_body" = "A small bonus will be awarded if you have more Brix than the statistical average. It's not much, but it will save you from blaming fate ;).

Don't forget to try Player vs Player mode: the rules are identical, but every 50 points you score you \"send\" a line of blox to the other player. The winner is the last one standing.

Finally: in Settings you can manage fonts, colours and sounds to make your BLOMIX experience as enjoyable as possible.";

